Rating: 4
We use this as our kitchen-sink soup of choice whenever we have a ham bone on hand. The barley is essential (although rice or beans works nearly as well), but after that, use whatever veggies you have on hand. We often use celery, carrots, corn, and peas and then we throw in spinach or kale if we have it in the fridge. It's a great way to use up the odds and ends of veggies that are sitting in your fridge. Absolutely delicious.

