Rating: 4
This was great! I've made twice, coincidentally exactly eight years apart. I guess now we know when it turns soup weather in NYC. I turned it into a real kitchen sink soup, using many of the suggestions from other reviewers and stuff I had on hand: -garlic (always) -kale -a little green pepper -fresh corn uncooked, just cut off the cob -the ham hocks gave good flavor, but no meat, so 1/2 pound of thick diced ham -used fresh tomatoes instead of canned -thyme as well as oregano -worstershire sauce -liquid smoke -tabasco - just a dash, so little yo can't really taste but somehow added something My husband was shocked that there were no beans, so I added 1 cup or so of small white beans. Of course, with all the extra ingredients, it needed extra broth/water. Too early for rutabaga at the NYC farmers' market, but I bet it would be great.

