Rating: 4
This is an excellent soup though I did make a few, mostly essential, alterations. Since I can't have barley, I used short-grain brown rice plus a small handful of wild rice, and that worked nicely. I thought about using kasha (also gluten free) but wondered if it would change the taste too much. Frozen black-eyed peas (from the garden) worked well in lieu of the green beans. Per the suggestion of another reviewer, I added fresh garlic and raggedly chopped green kale minus the hefty stems. The kale definitely gave this soup some character w/o overwhelming the flavor. Unlike cabbage, it retained its color and texture w/o getting mushy. Great soup!

